.TH "eeh_reset_device" 9 "eeh_reset_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
eeh_reset_device \- Perform actual reset of a pci slot
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" eeh_reset_device
.BI "(struct eeh_pe *pe "  ","
.BI "struct pci_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "struct eeh_rmv_data *rmv_data "  ","
.BI "bool driver_eeh_aware "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pe" 12
EEH PE
.IP "bus" 12
PCI bus corresponding to the isolcated slot
.IP "rmv_data" 12
Optional, list to record removed devices
.IP "driver_eeh_aware" 12
Does the device's driver provide EEH support?
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine must be called to do reset on the indicated PE.
During the reset, udev might be invoked because those affected
PCI devices will be removed and then added.
